chunks.text: Retrieval-Augmented Generation (RAG) retrieves relevant chunks and augments the prompt to improve factual grounding.

Rust is a systems programming language focused on safety, speed, and concurrency.
It is used for operating systems, web backends, game engines, CLI tools, and embedded.

Retrieval-Augmented Generation (RAG) combines a retriever (vector search) with a generator (LLM).
It improves factual accuracy by injecting relevant context chunks into the prompt.
